	(74,240,'Facts about the College',X'66616374732D61626F75742D7468652D636F6C6C656765','','<hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Facts\" />\r\n<p><img style=\"margin: 10px; float: right;\" title=\"title\" src=\"images/durant_quote.jpg\" alt=\"alt\" width=\"357\" height=\"238\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Facts About the College</h1>\r\n<p>The geosciences play an important role in the changing world through research, education, improved communications and implementation with other scientific and social disciplines.</p>\r\n<p>The realm of geosciences includes the scientific exploration of both planet Earth and its neighbors in space, the structure and processes of the atmosphere, oceans, land features and planetary features. Geosciences also explores human interactions with atmosphere, ocean and land environments.</p>\r\n<p>Geoscience also solves problems on the global scale.</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"accountability.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Geosciences Dashboard</a></h2>\r\n<table style=\"width: 85%;\" border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>Issues&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Answers&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>World population&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Sustainable development practice</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Pressure on natural resources</td>\r\n<td>New goesciences knowledge from research</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Environmental impacts</td>\r\n<td>Public policy and planning</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Environmental hazards</td>\r\n<td>Geoscience education and communication</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Academic Degrees\" />\r\n<h1>Academic Degrees and Initiatives</h1>\r\n<p>New academic initiatives for undergraduate students in the College of Geoscience include B.S. degrees offered in Environmental Studies, Environmental Geosciences, Geography with a Geographic Information Science option, and Spatial Sciences. Another recent offering is a minor in Geoinformatics (GIS/GPS/RS).</p>\r\n<hr id=\"system-readmore\" />\r\n<p><img title=\"globe in drop of water on leaf\" src=\"images/globe.jpg\" alt=\"globe in drop of water on leaf\" width=\"300\" height=\"450\" align=\"right\" border=\"1\" hspace=\"10\" vspace=\"10\" /></p>\r\n<p>New initiatives for graduate students include a Master of Geosciences degree (M.GSc.), M.S. and Ph.D. degrees in Water Management and Hydrologic Sciences, and Graduate Certificate in Petroleum Geosciences awarded to those earning a M.S. or Ph.D. in Geology.</p>\r\n<h2>Majors</h2>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://atmo.tamu.edu/\"><strong>Atmospheric Sciences</strong></a></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.S. Meteorology</li>\r\n<li>M.S. / Ph.D. Atmospheric Sciences</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://geography.tamu.edu\"><strong>Geography</strong></a></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.S. / M.S. / Ph.D. Geography</li>\r\n<li>B.S. Spatial Science</li>\r\n<li>B.S. Geography with GIS option</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://geoweb.tamu.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Geology &amp; Geophysics</strong></a></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.A. / B.S. Geology</li>\r\n<li>B.S. Geology / Engineering Geology option</li>\r\n<li>B.S. Geophysics</li>\r\n<li>M.S. / Ph.D. Geology</li>\r\n<li>M.S. / Ph.D. Geophysics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://ocean.tamu.edu\"><strong>Oceanography</strong></a></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>M.S. / Ph.D. Oceanography</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a href=\"undefined/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Interdisciplinary/College</strong></a></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>B.S. Environmental Geosciences</li>\r\n<li>B.S. Environmental Studies</li>\r\n<li>M.GSc. Geosciences</li>\r\n<li>M.S. / Ph.D. Water Management &amp; Hydrological Science</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Minors <br /></strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Earth Sciences</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Geosciences</li>\r\n<li>Environmental Studies</li>\r\n<li>Geography</li>\r\n<li>Geology</li>\r\n<li>Geophysics</li>\r\n<li>Geoinformatics</li>\r\n<li>Meteorology</li>\r\n<li>Oceanography</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Globalization\" />\r\n<h1>Globalization: A Natural Geoscience Focus</h1>\r\n<p>The College of Geosciences approaches all aspects of our mission – teaching, research, and outreach – from a global perspective. With 20% of our faculty, 17% of our total student population, and 37% of our graduate students being foreign born, thinking globally comes naturally to our college. Our students currently hail from more than 30 countries, and we have faculty from 11 countries.</p>\r\n<hr id=\"system-readmore\" />\r\n<p>The college has international Memorandums of Agreement with 13 institutions in 8 countries – Brazil, China, Ecuador, Egypt, Romania, Colombia, the United Kingdom and Japan. Our faculty and students conduct research focused on the land, air, sea and cultures of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>North, South and Latin America&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Western/Eastern Europe&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Middle East&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>South and East Asia&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Antarctica&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin: 10px; float: right;\" src=\"images/geothe_quote.jpg\" alt=\"Geothe Quote\" />The college is committed to helping our students understand the global context in which they will work. Here are some of our global programs and relationships.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>An initiative with Ocean University in Qingdao, China, offers a joint Ph.D. degree in oceanography. Ocean University students can work on their doctorates here, and our geosciences students have study opportunities in China.</li>\r\n<li>The college is also developing key research initiatives with Ocean University, the China Agricultural University, China University of Geosciences, Chinese Academy of Science, Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and Xiamen University.</li>\r\n<li>An agreement with the Oceanographic Institute of the Ecuadorean Navy (INOCAR) offers a faculty research exchange program, oceanography research cruises in the Galapagos aboard Ecuadorean Navy vessels, a training program for INOCAR officers, and plans to create an ocean observatory in the Galapagos.</li>\r\n<li>The college participates in international programs that provide long-term, integrated observations to improve predictions of climate change and its effects, minimize public health risks, sustain living resources and protect and restore healthy ecosystems.</li>\r\n<li>The college hosts the Regional Office of the Global Climate Observing System, which is one of twelve regional associations that comprise the U.S. Integrated Ocean Observing System which is part of the Global Ocean Observing System.</li>\r\n<li>Geosciences researchers are active in repeated and long-term ocean observing initiatives in the Southern Ocean, the Gulf of Oman, the Congo Canyon (Africa), and the Flower Garden Banks National Marine Sanctuary (Gulf of Mexico).</li>\r\n<li>Faculty members have many active projects in coastal Texas, the Gulf of Mexico, Costa Rica, Panama, the Galapagos, Palmyra Atoll, Equatorial Pacific, Nankai Trough, and Changjiang (Yangtze) river margin.</li>\r\n<li>The college maintains the Gulf Coast Repository, one of three worldwide repositories that are geologic ‘libraries’ of cores. Part of the Integrated Ocean Drilling Program, these repositories store over 330 kilometers of core samples drilled in the past 40 years by this ocean drilling program.</li>\r\n<li>Faculty research projects literally span the globe and beyond, with one Atmospheric Sciences professor serving on the science team for several NASA projects on Mars.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"GeoStatistics\" />\r\n<div class=\"grid_six\">\r\n<h1>GeoStatistics</h1>\r\n<h2><strong>Students (Fall 2010)</strong></h2>\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">693</td>\r\n<td>Undergraduate Students</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">354</td>\r\n<td>Graduate Students</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\"><strong>1047</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Employees</strong></h2>\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">104</td>\r\n<td>Tenured / Tenure-Track Faculty</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">7</td>\r\n<td>Instruct / Research Faculty</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">25</td>\r\n<td>Research Scientists</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">103</td>\r\n<td>Research Staff</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\">81</td>\r\n<td>Administrative Staff</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"right\"><strong>320</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"grid_six jblast\">\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Facilities</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Academics (Campus)</td>\r\n<td align=\"right\">204,289 sq. ft.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IODP (Research Park)</td>\r\n<td align=\"right\">87,067 sq. ft.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>GERG (Graham Road)</td>\r\n<td align=\"right\">23,522 sq. ft.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SEAG (Crystal Park)</td>\r\n<td align=\"right\">6,111 sq. ft.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Total <br /></strong></td>\r\n<td align=\"right\"><strong>320,989 sq. ft.</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>',-2,25,'2013-06-13 17:06:25',8,'','2013-07-11 17:43:40',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-06-13 17:06:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tag