	(103,297,'College Leadership Meeting: October 5, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6F63746F6265722D352D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: October 5, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>New TIAS call for nominations (North)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call for nominations for next year is forthcoming and will be due Nov. 30. We can nominate two.<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION ITEM: </strong> Submit nominee paperwork to Kate Miller by November 26. Keep her informed on your thinking in the meanwhile, in case there is a need for a \"competition\".</span></span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Time and Effort Reporting (Baldauf/Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Time and effort reporting is a continued issue. Faculty need to be much more timely in doing their approvals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> DHs to work with faculty on compliance with recording time on grants and certifying time and effort reports in a timely manner. For useful guidelines see </span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a href=\"http://as.vanderbilt.edu/docs/Understanding Effort Reporting.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Vanderbilt FAQs</a> and<a href=\"http://postaward.rutgers.edu/Vanderbilt_Audit.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> Vanderbilt Audit.</a></span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Hiring of Faculty who are Foreign Nationals (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If there is potential that a department will hire a foreign national for a tenure-track position, the ad for the position must be posted for 30 days in a \"national\" professional journal. This can be on a website or paper publication. Proof of publication must be retained and submitted with faculty hiring packet. Staff is checking on the large EOS ad to see if the 30-day position posting criteria will be met. For departments that did not post their faculty position in the large EOS ad, you must be sure to retain your proof of publication.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Departments must retain documentation of the 30 day posting as part of the search process. For more information you may refer to the Faculty Hiring Guidelines (pages 7 &amp; 8).</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Scholarship Policy (Bednarz)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft scholarship policies for the college, departments, and centers were distributed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Provide comments and/or updates to Sarah Bednarz by October 15.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>College Search Committee \"Training\" (Riggs)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Training now set for October 29, 12 pm.</li>\r\n<li>Request for time at faculty meeting to discuss climate survey results (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">All DHs should invite Eric Riggs to a faculty meeting for a ca. 20-30 minute presentation</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Development Director</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jack Falks will officially start October 15. He will attend GEODAC meeting October 12.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Deans\' Assistant</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sharon Alderete has resigned. Her last day is October 26. Position is posted and applications are rolling in.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>IODP Science Services Recompetition Proposal plans</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Texas A&amp;M will enter competition as a single entity. In these tight budget times, we judged this to be the only way to submit a sufficiently cost-effective proposal to maximize science output. Proposal oversight team is in place. LOI due Oct. 31; Full proposal due Jan. 22.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Potential effects of federal sequestration</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be aware that incoming federal funds for grants and contracts could be adversely affected if Congress does not act on sequestration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>ODASES Fellowships (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A proposal is on the table to designate the remaining ODASES Graduate Fellowship funds to be awarded as multi-year fellowships intended to recruit outstanding Ph.D. students to the ODASES related programs. Each award will consist of 2 years of ODASES funds with an in-kind match of 2 years support provided by the host department (TA, RA, scholarship funds, etc). Thus we intend to offer packages of 4 years support to 3 to 4 outstanding PhD applicants during the 2012-2013 recruiting season.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em>A<strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">CTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Give Jack Baldauf input by October 12</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Assessment – moving forward (Bednarz)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Congratulations on completing this year\'s cycle of assessment on time and at 100 percent completion on October 1.</li>\r\n<li></li>\r\n<li>In some cases, action plans are still too focused on improving the assessment process and not sufficiently centered on improving academic programs for students. This needs to change to make assessment efforts worthwhile and meet SACS criteria.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">DHs to touch base with departmental liaisons to discuss issues as appropriate. Sarah Bednarz stands ready to help.</span></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft revised undergraduate assessment plans for next year are due to Sarah Bednarz by November 1. This is the opportunity to create new/revised objectives, measures, and targets that will produce even more useful data. Sarah Bednarz stands ready to help.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEMS: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> DHs should touch base with departmental liaisons and make sure they are on track. Sarah Bednarz will distribute a worksheet to assist in revisions.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Department profiles needed at accountability.tamu.edu</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Department profiles nearly finished</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">DHs to submit corrections/additions to impact and productivity categories by October 12. Send to Kate Miller and Karen Riedel</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Provost\'s Enrollment Growth Incentive Plan</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plan distributed. College will be rewarded with a budget increase tied to a formula that involves SCHs, WSCHs, and number of graduates, provided that the University as a whole garners a revenue increase.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Post tenure review</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Post-tenure review policies for all departments have been approved by dean of faculties</li>\r\n<li>Department annual faculty review policies need to be amended with language describing what constitutes an \"overall unsatisfactory\". Recommended language was distributed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> DHs who have not yet discussed \"overall unsatisfactory\" criteria with faculty should do so, and notify Kate Miller by October 31 of faculty approval of new language.</span></em></p>\r\n<p>​</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:31:11',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','