	(104,298,'College Leadership Meeting: January 27, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6A616E756172792D32372D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: January 27, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>In Attendance: J. Baldauf, B. Bayer, S. Bednarz, K. Bowman, P. Chapman, D. Collins, R. Giardino, R. Kaiser, K. Miller, E. Riggs, V. Tchakerian</p>\r\n<p><strong>INFORMATION ITEMS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Texas Institute for Advanced Study (TIAS), J. North</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call for nominations, criteria, for TIAS fellows was discussed. Forms are available at: http://tias.tamu.edu/facultyfellows<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action: </strong> DHs to discuss with faculty and put forth nominations. Deadline: Feb. 17.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Risk Management Survey (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action:</strong> Baldauf to revise draft survey and send back out to DHs for comment</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Summer Budget (Bednarz/Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All requests to support summer teaching were honored. Funds are still available to teach two more courses – preferably upper division to help with time to degree for majors.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action:</strong> DHs should contact Bednarz ASAP, to add a course to the schedule.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Status of Searches (Relevant DHs)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not discussed - all underway</li>\r\n<li>Movement of 3-yr Review to spring</li>\r\n<li>DHs all approve move of third-year review of untenured faculty to spring. No faculty members affected for spring 2012</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action: </strong> Miller/Alderete to develop and send out proposed timeline for Spring 2013. Also to be posted on College Calendar</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Status of Annual Performance Evaluation Policies</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All prepared to submit revisions by Feb. 1</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action: </strong>DHs will send revisions to Miller, who will collate and forward for review and feedback from Dean of Faculties.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>DISCUSSION ITEMS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Measures of Impact and Productivity</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lengthy discussion of possible measures.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action: </strong>Baldauf to send out spreadsheet of possible metrics for review and comment by noon, Monday, Jan. 30.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Measure of College/Department Ranking</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>External rankings are either lacking or highly problematic for College and departments, with possible exception of USN&amp;WR ranking of Geology and Geophysics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action:</strong> Miller to provide provost with summary discussion</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Faculty Salary Savings (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not discussed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Teaching Buyout Policy</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action: </strong> Decision on College Policy: Buy out of a course equals 1.5 mo. salary</em></p>\r\n<p>​&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:33:11',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:33:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,11,'','',1,2,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(105,299,'College Leadership Meeting: February 27, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D66656272756172792D32372D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: February 27, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>In Attendance:&nbsp; J. Baldauf, B. Bayer, I. Szuynogh (for K. Bowman), P. Chapman, D. Collins, F. Marcantonio (for R. Giardino), R. Kaiser, K. Miller, V. Tchakerian</p>\r\n<p><strong>INFORMATION ITEMS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Academic Analytics Access</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All DHs are in receipt of access email from Academic Analytic</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>QEP – Commit to Communicate Roll Out – Dean to visit dept meetings - March</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION</strong>: </strong>Each department needs to schedule meeting time with Sharon Alderete</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Principal Investigator Policy (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION</strong></strong>: Jack to follow upo on Post doc as faculty equivalent positions and to summarize a college policy aligned with the university policy that PIs have to be faculty equivalent positions. Students could be listed on proposals, but a PI sponsor would be required.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Final FY 2013 Graduate Tuition Allocations (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bayer reviewed spreadsheet and allocation process in detail.&nbsp; Department Business Admins are already in receipt of this information.</li>\r\n<li>Review of FY 12 YTD tuition account balances shows we will be able to cover all tuition commitments for the year (including summer), and be able to support an additional 7 (GAT, GAR, or GANT) with tuition over the summer.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION:</strong></strong> Bayer to work with department business admins to optimize distribution of flexible and Ph.D. tuition funds among departments to zero out accounts by fiscal year’s end.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Review of Chairs and Professorships</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Faculty members awarded professorship in January 2010, will soon receive reporting and renewal application paperwork (handout)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Deans’ Council Review</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Energy Institute</li>\r\n<li>Steve Holditch to head reconstituted University Energy Institute– no longer an engineering activity VPR will be make significant seed funding for energy research available.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Latest on Accountability</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft metrics for System, University, and College distributed (handout).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION:</strong> </strong>DHs to give input on College metrics to Miller. DHs need to start defining what the department metrics will be.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>TIAS submissions</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CLGE submitted three nominations: one from OCNG, one from ATMO, one from GEPL (joint with PETE)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Status of Annual Performance Evaluation Policies</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Miller to visit with Dean of Faculties this week to review policies.</li>\r\n<li>Next steps forthcoming soon thereafter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Scholarship dinner – March 2</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Please RSVP, encourage faculty to attend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Parents Weekend – March 31</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breakfast buffet in lobby of O&amp;M 9:00 to 9:45; presentations by advisors &amp; faculty 9:50 to 10:30 focused on high impact educational opportunities; DHs, faculty representatives, advisors should attend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>DISCUSSION ITEMS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ratify New Vision, Mission</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So ratified</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION:</strong></strong></em><strong> Miller to give to Rumford to post</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Faculty Salary Savings/Teaching Buyout Policy (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Preliminary discussion ensued. To continue at budget retreat, March 2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Budget Meeting – your input</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION:</strong> </strong>DHs to deliver powerpoint slides no later than noon March 1. Earlier deliveries welcome.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Plans for Course Changes in Response to New Core Curriculum Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New core curriculum will require significant modifications to introductory general education courses in each department. Loss of SCHs is to College is a significant threat. Need to consider College wide strategy (handout). Funds will be available to support curriculum revision.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><strong>ACTION:</strong> </strong>DHs to alert faculty to situation. RFP for curriculum revision forthcoming. Need to visit possibility of College-wide task force.</em></p>\r\n<p>​&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:37:45',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:37:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,10,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(106,300,'College Leadership Meeting: March 30, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6D617263682D33302D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: March 30, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>SACS, SACS, SACS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SACS On-site Review Team on campus – April 2-5<span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION: </strong>be informed – see http://www.sacscoc.org and http://provost.tamu.edu/initiatives/quality-enhancement-plan</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Deans\' Council Review</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Research Grand Challenges</li>\r\n<li>Deans working together to delop short list that spans colleges and builds on our strengths. Will be tied into capital campaign. Energy and environment are likely themes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>TIAS Nomination</strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">One nomination from our college is making good progress in the review process</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Parents Weekend – March 31</strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION: </strong>Join us Saturday morning</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">College Advisory Council Meeting – April 11</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">DHs invited to dinner on April 11, tentative agenda handed out</span></li>\r\n<li>Communications opportunity – April = sustainability/environmental month for Texas A&amp;M – ideas to Karen Riedel by March 30</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Submit items to Karen Riedel</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>CPI member needed for Geosciences – Nominations close April 3<span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">DHs to solicit candidates</span></em></p>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Soltis Center Task Force</li>\r\n<li>Chris Houser to lead college task force</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTIONS: </span></strong></em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> DHs and directors to nominate a committee member for task force (1 from each dept and program). Miller to invite Pam Matthews to first meeting of task force. DHs will also attend that meeting.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Planning for Course Changes in Response to New Core Curriculum Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Principles</li>\r\n<li>Structure for moving forward</li>\r\n<li>Wide-ranging discussion. General agreement that we should work together. Considerable concern expressed about possible impact on GAT numbers and budgets (possibility of significantly fewer GATs or need for many more without a budget). Also considerable concern about the lack of a lab requirement at this stage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Miller to send note to Pam Matthews about these concerns after SACS On-site review is over.</span></em></p>\r\n<p>​</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:38:34',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:38:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,9,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(107,301,'College Leadership Meeting: April 27, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D617072696C2D32372D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: April 27, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chairs and Professorships event – May 3</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">67 attendees so far. Promises to be a great event</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Status of accountability data</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Data aggregation will be summer project for student supervised by Karen Riedel and Jack Baldauf</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Core Curriculum – Faculty Senate Agenda for Monday</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>3:15 pm, Rudder 301</li>\r\n<li>AFS nominations to be handled by GFAC</li>\r\n<li>Nominations for Hackerman Award in Chemical Research – Welch Foundation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION:</strong> Miller to inquire about University nomination procedure w/ DoF and then distribute response to DHs</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Research Administration Update (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>HPC status</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Preliminary concepts were presented to GEODAC and were favorably received. GEODAC established a subcommittee to assist in further development efforts. Discussions also commenced with the university to explore possible opportunities and strategies associated with this effort. The next GEODAC meeting will be late summer.</span></li>\r\n<li>Brazil / CONACYT type agreement</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Discussion continues with various colleges and the University concerning establishing a \"CONACYT\" type program with Brazil. Initial concepts would be for interested colleges to provide funds that would be matched by the VPR for collaborative research. Initial thoughts are that these funds would allow the annual award of about six $50K proposals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Center Reviews / status</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Two centers will be reviewed this year in keeping with current TAMU policies: Center for Tectonophysics and the Berg-Hughes Center.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><span>2. Approval will be requested to dissolve three Centers /Institutes: the Geodynamics Research Institute, the Earth Resource Institute, and the Cooperative Institute for Applied Meteorological Studies (as of 1 September 2012). In addition discussion has occurred concerning the possible reactivation of the Engineering Geosciences Center.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>New Members of College T&amp;P Committee</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTIONS:</strong> 1) Miller to review membership rules and send summary to DHS; 2) DHs to send new member names to Sharon Alderete by June 1.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Likely candidates for T&amp;P for FY 2013</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> DHs to send names of likely T&amp;P candidates for the coming year to Sharon Alderete as soon as they are known, presumably within the month</span></em></p>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Deans Council Update</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Discussion of implications of president\'s decision against asking for a tuition increase ensued</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Performance Evaluation Process and Merit Pool</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">CLGE Deans, Department Heads, and Directors to issue joint email re. internal merit compensation allocation process and value of our faculty and staff.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTIONS: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Miller to prepare statement for group review. Riedel to send to College.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Need for a CLGE Administrative open forum</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Consensus that none was needed at this time</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>​</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:39:26',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:39:26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,8,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(108,302,'College Leadership Meeting: May 18, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6D61792D31382D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: May 18, 2012</h1>\r\n<p><strong>2012-2013 GEOS Montague-CTE Scholars Call for Nominations:</strong> July 1, 2012 is the deadline to provide information to Sarah concerning nominations for consideration. Opportunity is open to one tenure-track assistant professor in each college. The award is a $6,500 grant to encourage further development of undergraduate teaching excellence.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bookstore Partnership: </strong>TAMU needs to comply with existing agreements to ensure accessibility and compliance with state and federal requirements for the selection, reporting and utilization of required and recommended course material in credit bearing courses. This is currently under judication and it is important that all material (books and other course material) is accessible through the bookstore. Per regulations this information is required 30 days prior to each semester. The bookstore will enter this information into a database and make this information accessible to all students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Update on Disbursement of Action 2015 Reallocation:</strong> The reallocation funds received in FY12 during the FY13 budget process are intended to be recurring based on successful performance metrics. The end of the year reports are due June 1, 2012 in the Provost office. Sarah Bednarz will produce this report given the short turnaround time. However, please note that a report is required to be submitted to Sarah from all recipients of reallocation funds. <strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">These reports need to be provided to Sarah no later than June 7, 2012.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>99 Hour Doctoral Cap Exemption:</strong> Request for exemptions has been submitted and the college has requested 27 exemptions. Exemptions are granted to the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board and can only be granted for academic reasons.<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> Department Heads and advisors are requested to monitor the progress of these students and other students in an effort to reduce the number of required future exemptions. Note that the State of Texas does not provide subvention to the University for students who have surpassed the 99 hour cap.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Bi-Annual Risk Assessment:</strong> A copy of the June 2012 College bi-annual risk assessment was circulated. The document provides the identified risks, an assessment of likelihood, and consequences of identified risks. Mitigation strategies for high and moderate risks are also included.&nbsp; There will be action items and tracking/monitoring associated with this assessment. Each risk identified has a corresponding mitigating activity and the person/position accountable for monitoring the mitigating activities.</p>\r\n<p><strong>OGS Academic Funds: </strong>OGS reporting for FY12 funding will be due on July 13, 2012.&nbsp; This will cover tuition, strategic support, and Grad Program Enhancement Funds (GPE). The Dean’s Office is currently reviewing summer tuition to balance accounts across the college. <strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Department Heads were asked to ensure strategic support funds are expended before August 31, 2012 and GPE funds are spent down to levels previously distributed to units.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Maestro Training:</strong> The initial Maestro Training courses were completed with about 15 college personnel participating. This number was lower than anticipated given the initial expression of interest. Additional training courses can be provided if there is interest.<strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; Department heads were asked to gauge interest in their units and provide that feedback to Barbara Bayer.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Concur Feedback:</strong> Several suggestions for improvement were mentioned: Issues concerning Concur should be forwarded to the unit Business administrator. This information will be compiled and forwarded to the University office as necessary.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Personnel Evaluations: </strong>Staff evaluations are required to be completed by the end of May. Faculty evaluations are required to be completed by June 16, 2012. Note that individuals need to have all TAMU/HR training assignments completed.<strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; Heads were reminded that evaluations for faculty must be completed before merit pay is distributed within their units.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Budget Request:</strong> Requests for FY2013 Budget requests should be submitted to Barbara no later than June 1, 2012. <strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Departments should provide their highest priorities items for consideration.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Message Distribution:</strong> All parties agreed to modify the current circulation of the announcement of potential funding proposals to improve efficiencies. In the future such announcements will be forward directly to faculty and research scientists.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Merit Worksheets: </strong>The merit process has been refined based on university clarification. Two funding pools will exist; a College self-funded 1.5% pool (reoccurring) and a 1.5% University funded one-time pool. These are both merit based pools. Any possible equity adjustments will be considered separately by the College. <strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Each department Head is requested to provide Barbara Bayer with a list of the unit’s equity priorities and recommendations.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>​</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:40:16',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:40:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,7,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(109,303,'College Leadership Meeting: July 20, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6A756C792D32302D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: July 20, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>New IDC Support Formula (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Implications of VPR\'s new IDC policy were discussed.<span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Barbara Bayer will prepare new College IDC policy based on VPR\'s university policy. This policy will be retroactive to IDC earned starting March 1, 2012 which is typically distributed in November.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>System Faculty Evaluation Project (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">All departments are to send requested evaluation data to Barbara Bayer by Friday, August 3rd.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>FY 2013 Appointment Letters (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft letters distributed for review</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Barbara Bayer will provide departments with finalized offer letter templates and final merit (one-time and recurring) along with approved equity information. Letter templates and merit information will be provided to departments within the first few weeks of August for distribution to faculty and staff by August 31, 2012.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Annual Faculty Evaluation Policies</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Approved by Dean of Faculties and posted on CLGE website</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Half Day Assessment Workshop for CLGE</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Will take place August 29 at 1 pm, all assessment liaisons and department heads to attend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Core Curriculum Changes Time line</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Handouts provided. College/Departments will not engage in planning until more concrete input is provided from central administration re. lab requirements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Tentative T&amp;P time line </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Tentative\" time line distributed – IS THE OFFICIAL TIME LINE (per Sharon Alderete).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Tchakerian to prepare proposed time line for spring midterm review by Aug. 6.</span></em></p>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Needs for meeting University Global Leadership goals</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hand out provided. Input needed on how departments/college plan to meet university global leadership goals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Input to S. Bednarz by July 31.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Post-tenure Review – Steps to put College Policy in place</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Consensus that college criteria for receiving an overall unsatisfactory in an annual review / post-tenure review are: a) unsatisfactory performance in teaching, and b) unsatisfactory in any two among teaching</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tchakerian to draft proposed policy on department procedures for post-tenure review by July 31. Bowman and Chapman to review. Provide result to Miller by Aug. 3.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Accountability Data Compilation and Fact Sheets</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Miller to distribute digital data compiled over the summer by communications staff to department heads</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Defining Excellence Metrics for Accountability Dashboard</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Consensus that proposed College Dashboard is reasonable</li>\r\n<li>Consensus that each department should have 8-10 measures of excellence with respect to impact and productivity. About half of these will be common to other departments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Department Heads to provide 4-8 preferred department-specific preferred measures by August 10. These should be measures that the unit want</span></em></p>\r\n<p>​</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:41:04',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:41:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,6,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(110,304,'College Leadership Meeting: August 24, 2012',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6175677573742D32342D32303132','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: August 24, 2012</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delegation of Authority (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discussed revised process for delegation of authority for department heads in their absence. Template was handed out</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">Action Item: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Barbara Bayer will send a word template to Departments. Departments to provide delegation of authority letters to Barbara Bayer by Aug. 31.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Year-end Account Clean-up (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Departments should clean up negative balances. Those corrected today, are guaranteed to be effective at fiscal year\'s end. Department Heads will be copied on future e-mail to business staff regarding unresolved negative account balances.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Account balances (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Departments should be putting a priority on using the UFO process where at all possible/appropriate.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>FY13 Budget Requests (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Nearly all department requests were funded.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Bayer will distribute approved budget request documentation. Fund transfers will occur after the FY13 budget rolls (mid-September).</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>OCNG/GERG (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Request for TAMU approval to hire for each position is in progress</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Draft advertisement is being reviewed by search committees</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>IT (Baldauf)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Several items in progress (1) IT manager position being finalized, (2) IT liaison roles &amp; responsibilities being defined, and (3) Departmental IT specialist under discussion</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Short Courses (Bednarz)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Policy: No short courses. Stacked courses are okay.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Assessment Workshop for CLGE – Aug. 29, 1- 5pm (Bednarz)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Materials for Aug. 29 workshop for department assessment liaisons and heads were distributed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Next steps for assessment were discussed in light of SACS evaluation.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Core Curriculum Changes Time line Update</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Need for department action likely delayed until spring.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Faculty Senate Election</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Another Geoscience representative is needed, preferably from ATMO or GEPL (OCNG, GEOG already represented).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM: </strong>Contact Wendy Jepson ASAP</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>DH Council Items (Chapman)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chapman to continue as College representative to University DH Council. Other DHs are willing to sub as needed</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">FCOI training is rolling out on Traintraq</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Undergraduate degree planner system being developed. S. Bednarz and E. Dykes are on university committee that is providing feedback.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Advisory Council Agenda, DO search update</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft agenda for College Advisory Council Meeting on September 7 distributed. Emphasis on communications and the upcoming campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Search for a new development officer is progressing. Screening interviews took place in late July and will occur again in the next couple weeks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Post-tenure review document</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><em><strong> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">ACTION ITEM: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Miller to forward DHs\' consensus document to Dean of Faculties</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Excellence Metrics</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Still waiting on input from all DHs. Miller and Riedel will assemble.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>​</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:41:47',8,'','2013-07-11 19:52:54',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:41:47','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,5,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(111,305,'College Leadership Meeting: January 11, 2013',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6A616E756172792D31312D32303133','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: January 11, 2013</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Retreat Preparation – Development (Falks)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 78px;\"><em><strong>Action Item:</strong> Unit Heads should provide 3-5 items for discussion at January 23 retreat using templates provided by Jack Falks</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Insights into Philanthropy Workshop – Feb. 6 (Falks)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All heads and directors encouraged to attend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 78px;\"><em><strong>Action item:</strong> Those who can attend should let Jack Falks know by Monday, January 14.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Human Resources Protocols for Hiring (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Handout: TAMU Search Committee Guide for Non-Faculty Positions</li>\r\n<li>DHs are reminded that procedures in the guide must be followed carefully, including documentation of process.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 78px;\"><em><strong>Action item:</strong> DHs should remind faculty supervisors of the guidelines. Barbara Bayer will remind department business administrators.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>3G PDF Form (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Form under development and testing, designed to streamline accountability data collection process while minimizing impact on faculty time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Budget reallocation for FY14</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>0.65% of College\'s state budget will be returned to central administration in FY 14 as part of president\'s reallocation process.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Assessment Status (DHs)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not discussed due to time constraints</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Core Curriculum Submissions Status (DHs)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The following courses are being prepared for submission to Faculty Senate: OCNG 251/252; ATMO 201/202; GEOS 210; GEOL 101, 104, 106; GEOG 201, 202, 203, 205. GEOS 105 will move forward in the next cycle.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Summer/Fall Schedule (Bednarz)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>DHs should prioritize summer course funding requests by 1) impact of offering on reducing time to degree for majors, 2) WSCHs, 3) University service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 78px;\"><em><strong>Action Item:</strong> Due Wednesday, January 16</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Temporary Reassignment of Sonia Garcia\'s duties</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dr. Garcia is out on FMLA leave, see hand out for who has been reassigned her duties</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Reorganization of College Communications functions</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>College Communication reporting has been reorganized to improve alignment with strategic plan and priority setting. Jennifer Rumford now reports to Karen Riedel. All work requests go through Karen Riedel.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Retreat Agenda</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>See Handout: January 23: main topics are development planning, business workflow, budget, enrollment, and accountability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>IODP Re-competition Update</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Re-competition proposal to be submitted next week. Proposal is in excellent shape. IODP staff has done an excellent job. Central administration has been extremely helpful throughout.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>President\'s Preeminent Faculty Initiative, CRI</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CLGE involved in Energy and Environment themes. Announcement on path forward on searches related to Berg-Hughes Center Director and ground water will occur within next couple of weeks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Upcoming Dean\'s Review</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kate Miller has agreed to be considered for another term as Dean. Usual TAMU review process will begin within a month.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Need for textbook policy(ies)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not discussed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>​&nbsp;</p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:47:50',8,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:47:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,3,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(112,306,'College Leadership Meeting: February 22, 2013',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D66656272756172792D32322D32303133','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: February 22, 2013</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business functions reorganization update (Bayer)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Reorganization of College business functions is proceeding. Business staff will have a retreat March 8. Functions will begin to transition in April and will continue throughout the summer. Meetings will continue weekly to develop the strategies and processes. Barbara Bayer asked department heads to begin to schedule her for faculty meetings in March.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare for April 12 budget retreat (Bayer)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Barbara Bayer sent all unit heads a FY14 budget request form in PDF format as well as an Ops Funding Requirement worksheet. All FY14 budget requests and Ops funding worksheets are due to Barbara Bayer by March 22, 2013. This information will be reviewed and prioritized at the April 12 budget retreat. Department Heads indicated they may meet to discuss ways to trim their ops budgets to help mitigate the funding reduction we will experience in FY14.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Course buyout policy (Bayer)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">A College wide course buyout policy was approved by the executive committee it and will be posted on the web</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Diversity funding (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">The College continues to be rewarded with funding for progress in diversity. $7K in diversity funds will be distributed to departments for graduate recruitment.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Workplace Climate taskforce (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Members of a College taskforce to review data from the 2011 climate survey have been recommended. Initial requests have been sent to prospective members, intending first meeting before Spring Break, latest right after. Recommendations by semester end to the Dean.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Admissions update (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Weekly admission data for undergraduates was handed out. All programs except ENGS have seen an increase in admitted students and an increase in confirmed acceptances over this time last year. It is still early in the season, but this is a good sign. Additionally, acceptances by Hispanic, Black and Asian students are also up relative to this time last year.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>HPC Update (Baldauf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">President Loftin has awarded $2 M in AUF monies to College and TAMU CIS for a major high performance computing upgrade contingent on a more detailed planning document.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Jack Baldauf is working on the planning document</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Emeritus Nominations due April 22</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Submit nomination packages to Janet Kling by April 5, 2013, so the dean may prepare letters of recommendation that must accompany the package.<br /></em>Guidelines and step by step instructions can be found at: <a href=\"http://dof.tamu.edu/sites/default/files/tenure_promotion/Emeritus_guidelines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">http://dof.tamu.edu/sites/default/files/tenure_promotion/Emeritus_guidelines.pdf</a>.<br />All packages must include the Recommendation for Emeritus Status Cover Sheet that may be found at: <a href=\"http://dof.tamu.edu/sites/default/files/tenure_promotion/Recommendation_for_Emeritus_Status.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">http://dof.tamu.edu/sites/default/files/tenure_promotion/Recommendation_for_Emeritus_Status.pdf</a><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set dates for dean to visit w/ dept/program faculty March-April</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Janet Kling will contact departments to schedule.</em></p>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Engineering 25x25 Sub-committee members</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Kate Miller is on the Steering Committee</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Sarah Bednarz, Eric Riggs, and Rick Giardino (or designee) to participate on sub-councils</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>AAU STEM Initiative (Bednarz)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">All departments with undergraduate programs will participate.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>Action ITEM:</strong> DHs to submit names of two participating faculty members to Kate Miller by noon on 2/25.</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gaging Department Performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Lengthy discussion on how we assess departmental performance</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> DHs to meet w/ Kate Miller on 2/25 to finalize subset of metrics for expectations and excellence for submission to Provost.</em></p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:49:45',8,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:49:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,2,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(113,307,'College Leadership Meeting: March 22, 2013',X'636F6C6C6567652D6C6561646572736869702D6D656574696E672D6D617263682D32322D32303133','<h1>College Leadership Meeting: March 22, 2013</h1>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ITEMS</p>\r\n<p><strong>Business functions reorganization update (Bayer)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Things moving along. Complex process. Department staff digging in and working hard to make it a reality</li>\r\n<li>3G in PDF format update (Bayer)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Draft form works.<br /><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Barbara Bayer will distribute form in PDF and Excel formats to DHs.</em><br /><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Barbara Bayer\'s office will prepare data off of 3Gs in Microsoft Word format for those forms already submitted.</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Input on Staff Evaluations: to/from Dean\'s office</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Dean\'s Office personnel will provide comments on department staff as appropriate to DHs by April 15</em><br /><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> DHs will provide comments on Dean\'s office staff to Dean\'s Office supervisors as appropriate by April 15</em><br /><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Kate Miller will provide direction to DHs and Dean\'s Office Supervisors<br /></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advisory Council Meeting / Scholarship Dinner, April 5</li>\r\n<li>AAU STEM Project Update (Bednarz)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Broad and active participation across the College. Final proposal will be distributed.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Self report of GRE/TOEFL score (Bednarz)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Recommend policy of having GRE/TOEFL scores in hand before student arrives at Texas A&amp;M</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>On-line MS, MOOC update (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Meeting onsite with Embanet-Compass and Bisk education 4/26-29 – should return with firmer options and proposals for action from their perspective.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">University MOOC committee is nearing recommendations – should be complete by mid-May.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>College Climate Taskforce Update (Riggs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Comprised of 9 faculty and staff members from around the College. First meeting went well. 1-2 more meetings expected, one in latest April and the final one in mid-May. Recommendations for follow up actions to Dean by end of finals week.</p>\r\n<p>DISCUSSION ITEMS</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>International Connections Update (all)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Status of recent College connections with Brazil, China, Costa Rica, Ecuador, and Mexico was reviewed in a roundtable style. All areas remain active.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Continuity of department assessment liaisons</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Acknowledgement by group that continuity is important in this position. DHs agree that appointments should be for 2-3 years, to optimize corporate knowledge.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Credit\" for first year seminars</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> DHs to consult within departments re. student retention and interest in continuing First Year Seminars and under what circumstances.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Sarah Bednarz to convene meeting of DHs and faculty undergraduate advisors in 2-3 weeks to discuss retention programs, First Year and Transfer Seminars.</em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provost\'s Instructions re. Department Matrix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\">Group effort by DHs to quantify metrics met provost expectations</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> DHs to submit corrections to Kate Miller by noon on 3/25.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><em><strong>ACTION ITEM:</strong> Kate Miller will submit info to provost. Input will be sought from DHs as necessary.</em></p>','',-2,47,'2013-07-11 19:50:36',8,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-11 19:50:36','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,1,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
