	(135,331,'Visiting Geosciences',X'7669736974696E672D67656F736369656E636573','<h2>Visiting Geosciences</h2>\r\n<p>Prospective students can tour the College of Geosciences from 2 to 3 p.m., Friday during fall, spring and summer semesters.</p>\r\n<p>To register for a tour:<br />979.845.5851 | visit@tamu.edu</p>\r\n<p>You can also complete a reservation form online at <a href=\"http://visit.tamu.edu\">Appelt Aggieland Visitor Center.</a> Designate \"Tour Geosciences\" in the box marked \"Additional Comments or Questions for the Visitor Center Staff.\"</p>\r\n<p>Need more information?<br />recruiting@geosciences.tamu.edu</p>','',1,45,'2013-07-16 21:13:05',8,'','2013-07-17 21:03:41',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-16 21:13:05','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',2,4,'','',1,5,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(136,332,'Apply',X'6170706C79','','<hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Before You Apply\" />\r\n<h1>Apply</h1>\r\n<h2>Before You Apply</h2>\r\n<p>You will do best in the geosciences if you follow these steps:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take seven semesters of math in high school</li>\r\n<li>Receive 1200 or better on the SAT math and verbal sections</li>\r\n<li>Participate in extracurricular activities</li>\r\n<li>Research majors in geosciences and understand the discipline</li>\r\n<li>Do your homework. Research the degrees, requirements and subjects you are likely to take.</li>\r\n<li>Ask questions. You will find contact information for our advisors on the Advisor page.</li>\r\n<li>Visit the campus and the college. See the [Visiting Geosciences] web page. [to link with the web page]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr id=\"system-readmore\" /><hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Freshman Application\" />\r\n<h2>Freshman Application</h2>\r\n<p>Incoming freshmen apply through the <a href=\"https://www.applytexas.org/adappc/gen/c_start.WBX\" target=\"_blank\">Texas Common Application (Apply Texas) website.</a></p>\r\n<p>Explore this site for a lot of helpful information.</p>\r\n<p>Another site that will help you specifically with Texas A&amp;M is the <a href=\"http://admissions.tamu.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Office of Admissions.</a></p>\r\n<p>The best advice we can give is to apply early. Your early application will increase your chances of getting the college and course of study you want.</p>\r\n<hr id=\"system-readmore\" /><hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"After You Apply\" />\r\n<h2>After You Apply</h2>\r\n<p>After you apply, here\'s what happens next.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>You can <a href=\"https://applicant.tamu.edu/Login.aspx?ReturnUrl=/Secure/ApplicantInfo.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">check your application and records online.</a></li>\r\n<li>After you receive your acceptance package in the mail (congratulations and welcome to the College of Geosciences), <a href=\"https://applicant.tamu.edu/Login.aspx?ReturnUrl=/Secure/ApplicantInfo.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">return to your online records</a> and accept your admission or return the admission card in your acceptance package.</li>\r\n<li>Sign up for <a href=\"http://newaggie.tamu.edu\" target=\"_blank\">New Student Conferences.</a> This conference is mandatory and you can select from several dates throughout the summer. Your parents are encouraged to attend with you.</li>\r\n<li>Your next stop is the <a href=\"http://admissions.tamu.edu/files/pubs/NTYA_Freshman_09.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Now That You Are Admitted website,</a> which has tons of useful information on housing, immunizations, scholarships, emergency loans, part-time jobs and dozens of on- and off-campus resources.</li>\r\n</ol><hr id=\"system-readmore\" /><hr class=\"system-pagebreak\" title=\"Transfer Students\" />\r\n<h2>Transfer Students</h2>\r\n<p>We actively seek and welcome qualified transfer students through the traditional transfer admission pathway (admissions.tamu.edu/transfer). In fact, <a href=\"http://www.agiweb.org/workforce/Currents/Currents-73-TXCCtoUniv.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Texas A&amp;M is the No. 1 university in Texas</a> for students transferring into the geosciences from other universities and community colleges.</p>\r\n<p>The College is also an active partner in Texas A&amp;M\'s <a href=\"http://admissions.tamu.edu/PSA/\" target=\"_blank\">Program for System Admission (PSA)</a> and the <a href=\"http://admissions.tamu.edu/pta/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Program for Transfer Admission (PTA).</a></p>\r\n<p>Each degree program in the College has specific requirements for admission. You can find information on the courses you need to take before admission is available on the College of Geosciences transfer page [geosciences.tamu.edu/academics/transfer-students]. Pay special attention to the Transfer Admission Worksheet to plan your courses in order to be successful in your transfer.</p>\r\n<p>Successful applicants will</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>have a 3.0 or better GPA</li>\r\n<li>have completed at least one course in their prospective major</li>\r\n<li>be mathematically and science-literate as demonstrated through completion of several courses specified by each major.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Associate Dean for Academic Affairs in the College of Geosciences makes the decision on admissions in consultation with faculty and academic advisors. The college works closely with the Student Learning Center in programs to help students make a successful transition in the College of Geosciences.</p>',1,45,'2013-07-16 22:17:09',8,'','2013-07-17 21:17:56',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-16 22:17:09','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',4,3,'','',1,30,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(137,333,'iGeo',X'6967656F','<h2>iGeo</h2>\r\n<p>Every fall we offer a three-day weekend program to introduce students to the college and to Texas A&amp;M. This year, <a href=\"http://igeo.tamu.edu\">iGeo is Oct. 17–19, 2013.</a></p>','',1,45,'2013-07-17 21:05:35',8,'','2013-07-17 21:12:22',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-17 21:05:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',2,2,'','',1,5,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(138,334,'GeoX',X'67656F78','<h2>GeoX</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://geox.tamu.edu\">GeoX, our weeklong program</a> is each June. Students live in a dorm, take classes and have lab exercises, go on field trips and experience life in Aggieland at around campus and the Brazos Valley.</p>','',1,45,'2013-07-17 21:06:18',8,'','2013-07-17 21:12:01',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-17 21:06:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',2,1,'','',1,2,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\",\"tags\":null}',0,'*',''),
	(139,335,'Aggieland Saturday',X'61676769656C616E642D7361747572646179','<h1>Aggieland Saturday</h1>\r\n<p><span class=\"wf_caption\" style=\"margin: 10px; float: right; display: inline-table;\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid #000000; margin: auto;\" src=\"images/events/aggieland.jpg\" alt=\"aggieland\" /><span style=\"max-width: 300px; padding: 3px; display: block;\">Aggieland Saturday is a chance to meet professors and learn about the College of Geosciences.</span></span>Aggieland Saturday, is a campus wide event for students and their families. You will learn about all Texas A&amp;M has to offer – from our great academics to the indescribable Aggie Spirit.</p>\r\n<p>The College of Geosciences provides a full day of events to introduce you to life as an Aggie and as a geosciences student. You and your parents will learn about the geosciences from our faculty and students, take a tour of our facilities and talk to academic advisors and representatives from Texas A&amp;M Admissions and Financial Aid offices.</p>\r\n<p>Watch for more information on this site and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://admissions.tamu.edu/aggielandsaturday/\" target=\"_blank\">Aggieland Saturday at Texas A&amp;M.</a></p>\r\n<p>Contact information for the College of Geosciences<br />Dr. Sonia Garcia, Director of Recruitment<br />979.845.3651 | garcias5@tamu.edu.</p>','',1,45,'2013-07-17 21:11:27',8,'','2013-07-22 15:45:37',8,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-07-17 21:11:27','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show